text.__SUMMARY__: Eucalyptus stowardii, commonly known as fluted-horn mallee, is a mallee tree that is native to Western Australia.The mallee or sometimes tree will typically grow to a height of 2.5 to 7 metres (8 to 23 ft) and has smooth bark. It blooms between June and November producing conflorescences with cream-white flowers.It is found on stony rises, limestone hills and road verges in the Wheatbelt region of Western Australia where it grows in gravelly sand-loam soils.
